se.code77.jq.config

Class Config

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.code77.jq.config.Config
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AndroidConfig

    public abstract class Config
extends java.lang.Object
    Configuration for JQ. The configuration offers integration points into the host environment, as well as tweaking of behaviour.

      • monitorUnterminated

        public final boolean monitorUnterminated
        Set to true if unterminated promise chains should cause warnings to be logged. An unterminated promise chain is a chain of promises ending with a promise that has produced a result (fulfilled or rejected) without anyone observing it and without explicitly terminating the chain with Promise.done().

      • getConfig

        public static Config getConfig()
        Get the configuration used by JQ. If no configuration is explicitly given through setConfig(Config), JQ will attempt to create a default configuration if the host environment can be detected. Otherwise an exception will be thrown.
        Returns:
        Current configuration

      • createDispatcher

        public Config.Dispatcher createDispatcher()
        Create a dispatcher for the current thread. Dispatchers are registered through #registterDispatcher(Thread, Dispatcher) but the exact behavior may differ for various Config implementations (e.g. there may be a default dispatcher, or the call may cause an error).

        Dispatcher
